---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About SPHERE — Human Rights & Digital Advocacy"
  description="Learn about SPHERE: Born from the 2022 People's Struggle, we bridge human rights advocacy and community action in Sri Lanka through research, training, and strategic interventions."
>
  <main class="page page-animate">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="section section--hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="hero">
          <div>
            <div class="hero__eyebrow">About SPHERE</div>
            <h1 class="hero__title text-balance">
              Sustaining the momentum of civic participation in Sri Lanka
            </h1>
            <p class="hero__desc">
              We are SPHERE — Society for the Progress, Human Rights, Empowerment & Equity.
              Born from the 2022 People's Struggle, we work to prevent a slide back into civic
              passivity by connecting human rights advocacy with community-level action.
            </p>

          </div>
          <div>
            <img
              src="/hero-visual.png"
              alt="SPHERE advocacy illustration"
              class="hero__panel"
              style="width: 100%; max-width: 500px; border-radius: var(--radius-lg); box-shadow: var(--shadow-xl);"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Our Story -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="grid-2">
          <div>
            <h2 class="section__title">Our Story</h2>
            <p class="section__kicker">From protest to durable participation</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              SPHERE was created to prevent a slide back into civic passivity after the 2022
              people's struggle. The uprising demonstrated the power of collective action,
              but sustaining that energy requires institutional support and strategic coordination.
            </p>
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px;">
              We connect human rights advocacy with community-level action—standing up for
              freedom of expression, association, and privacy while strengthening everyday
              democratic practice throughout Sri Lanka.
            </p>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What We Do -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section__title" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 32px;">
          What We Do
        </h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="icon-box">
            <div class="icon-box__icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M12 3v18"/>
                <path d="M5 6h14"/>
                <path d="M5 12h14"/>
                <path d="M5 18h14"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="icon-box__content">
              <h3>Advocacy</h3>
              <p>
                Strategic interventions with regulators and institutions. We file public interest
                complaints, engage in evidence-led campaigns, and monitor cases affecting civil
                liberties and democratic rights.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="icon-box">
            <div class="icon-box__icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M14.5 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V7.5L14.5 2z"/>
                <polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/>
                <path d="M12 18v-6"/>
                <path d="M8 15h8"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="icon-box__content">
              <h3>Research</h3>
              <p>
                Legal and policy analysis on digital rights through the Centre for Digital Policy
                Research (CDPR). We produce briefs, policy papers, and evidence to inform
                public debate and legislative reform.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="icon-box">
            <div class="icon-box__icon">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/>
                <path d="M6 12v5c3 3 9 3 12 0v-5"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="icon-box__content">
              <h3>Training</h3>
              <p>
                Capacity-building through <em>Our Rights – Our Future</em> and similar programs.
                We empower communities, defenders, and activists with knowledge about their
                rights, digital security, and advocacy strategies.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Vision, Mission & Values -->
    <section class="section" style="background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(2, 132, 199, 0.04), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6), rgba(0, 163, 130, 0.04)); position: relative;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section__title" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 8px;">
          Vision, Mission & Values
        </h2>
        <p class="section__kicker" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
          Our guiding principles and purpose
        </p>
        
        <!-- Vision & Mission -->
        <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto 40px;">
          <div class="vision-mission-card">
            <h3>Vision</h3>
            <p>
              "A world where human rights are universally upheld through active public participation, ensuring all individuals, groups and people can exercise their fundamental freedoms with safety, and dignity across an inclusive and non-discriminatory physical and digital frontier."
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="vision-mission-card">
            <h3>Mission</h3>
            <p>
              "To empower diverse communities to defend and advance human rights by providing the tools, knowledge, and platforms necessary for active participation. We bridge the gap between physical and digital freedoms through inclusive advocacy, non-discriminatory technology standards, and grassroots mobilization. By striving for continuous progress, driving systemic policy reforms, and holding institutional powers accountable, we ensure safety, dignity, and justice for all."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Values -->
        <h3 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 24px; font-size: 20px; color: var(--text);">Our Core Values</h3>
        <div class="values-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 16px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Inclusive</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We embrace diversity and ensure all voices are heard, creating spaces where everyone can participate meaningfully in defending human rights.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Progressive</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We continuously evolve our approaches and strategies to address emerging challenges in human rights and digital freedoms.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Transparency and Accountability</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We operate openly, publishing our policies, funding sources, and activities to maintain public trust and demonstrate our commitment to accountability.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Dignity and Tolerance</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We uphold the inherent dignity of every person and practice tolerance, respecting diverse perspectives while standing firm on human rights principles.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Equality and Equity</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We strive for both equal treatment and equitable outcomes, recognizing that justice requires addressing systemic barriers and historical inequalities.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Integrity and Empathy</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We act with unwavering integrity while maintaining empathy for those we serve, ensuring our advocacy is both principled and compassionate.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="value-card">
            <h4 class="value-card__title">Meritocracy and Technocracy</h4>
            <p class="value-card__content">
              We value expertise and evidence-based approaches, making decisions based on merit and technical knowledge to maximize our impact.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <style>
      @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .values-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
        }
      }
    </style>

    <!-- Our Journey -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section__title" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 8px;">Our Journey</h2>
        <p class="section__kicker" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">Building from the grassroots up</p>
        
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-item__year">2022</div>
            <div class="timeline-item__content">
              The People's Struggle (Aragalaya) demonstrates unprecedented civic participation
              across Sri Lanka, calling for systemic reform and accountability.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-item__year">2023–2024</div>
            <div class="timeline-item__content">
              Planning and groundwork for SPHERE begins. Core team members come together
              with a shared vision to sustain civic engagement and defend human rights.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-item__year">2025</div>
            <div class="timeline-item__content">
              SPHERE officially established to institutionalize the momentum of civic action.
              Centre for Digital Policy Research (CDPR) launched as our legal-policy engine.
              Name reservation approved for <em>SPHERE Research and Advocacy</em>.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-item__year">2025–2026</div>
            <div class="timeline-item__content">
              First strategic interventions filed including HRCSL complaints and RTI requests.
              Scaling training programs, completing legal registration, and launching
              national digital rights campaigns through CDPR.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Our Team -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="section__title" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 8px;">
          Our Team
        </h2>
        <p class="section__kicker" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
          Passionate advocates for justice and digital rights
        </p>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <!-- Anuruddha Bandara -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/anuruddha_bandara.png"
              alt="Anuruddha Bandara"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Anuruddha Bandara</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Anuruddha, a graduate with a BSc (Hons) in Science and Management from the University of Colombo and currently reading for Attorney-At-Law at Sri Lanka Law College. He is a passionate social activist and is a major advocate for digital rights. Anuruddha's professional experience spans roles in election monitoring, political advocacy. He has been actively involved in promoting youth participation in politics. He has also participated in international electoral missions in and fellowships in Nepal, Indonesia and Australia.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Kasun Indika -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/kasun_indika.png"
              alt="Kasun Indika"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Kasun Indika</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Kasun is a software engineering professional and technology consultant with a strong passion for political and social justice, human rights, digital freedom, and cyber activism. He is a co-founder of the Internet Freedom Movement – Sri Lanka, a platform dedicated to defending online rights and promoting internet freedom.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tharushi Dishara -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/tharushi_dishara.png"
              alt="Tharushi Dishara"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Tharushi Dishara</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Tharushi is a Attorney At Law and a dedicated human rights defender committed to justice and equality. She currently works with the Centre for Society and Religion (CSR) and the Law and Society Trust (LST), where she focuses on key issues such as police brutality, labor rights, and marginalized communities' access to justice.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Nathali Rangajeewa -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/nathali_rangajeewa.png"
              alt="Nathali Rangajeewa"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Nathali Rangajeewa</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Nathali is a political and social activist and she has recently completed BSc in Psychology and Counseling. Nathali is committed to creating lasting, positive change in our community with a mission to bridge the gap between mental well-being and societal development, recognizing that both are integral to the progress of any nation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Angela Nanayakkara -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/angela_nanayakkara.png"
              alt="Angela Nanayakkara"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Angela Nanayakkara</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Angela is a passionate human rights enthusiast and a dedicated volunteer at the Kandy Human Rights Office, where she has emerged as a prominent advocate for justice and equality. Angela's unwavering commitment to amplifying the voices of marginalized communities has made her a key figure in Sri Lanka's contemporary social justice movements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Sathya Charith -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/sathya_charith.png"
              alt="Sathya Charith"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Sathya Charith</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Sathya is a highly accomplished Marketing Professional and Social Justice Advocate, uniquely positioned at the intersection of strategic business management and digital grassroots mobilization. Holding a Post Graduate Diploma from the Chartered Institute of Marketing (CIM, UK) and an MBA from the University of Bedfordshire (UK), he brings a sophisticated, global perspective to every campaign he leads. He is a passionate specialist in social media campaigning, leveraging digital platforms as powerful tools for social equity and justice.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Lahiru Lakmina Fernando -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/lahiru_lakmina.png"
              alt="Lahiru Lakmina Fernando"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Lahiru Lakmina Fernando</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Lahiru is a Business Information Systems undergraduate at the University of Sri Jayewardenepura (USJP), specializing in social media and digital solutions. A passionate advocate for digital rights, he is dedicated to leveraging technology to champion online freedoms and ethical digital practices.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Sherene -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/placeholder_1.png"
              alt="Sherene"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Sherene Dias</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Sherene is an Information Systems undergraduate at the University of Colombo School of Computing and an AAT Passed Finalist reading for Chartered Accountancy. With three years of professional audit experience, she specializes in the intersection of finance and technology. She is a dedicated advocate for human rights, committed to promoting transparency and accountability in business.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Pubudu Viduranga -->
          <div class="team-card">
            <img
              src="/team/placeholder_2.png"
              alt="Pubudu Viduranga"
              class="team-card__image"
            />
            <div class="team-card__content">
              <h3 class="team-card__name">Pubudu Viduranga</h3>
              <p class="team-card__bio">
                Pubudu is a Marketing Executive and Student Counsellor at Asian International Academy, holding a Master’s in Sociology and a degree in Mass Media. With a strong background in child rights advocacy and social research, he specializes in community mobilization and youth empowerment. He is passionate about driving social impact through effective communication and development initiatives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


  </main>
</BaseLayout>
